==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Handling
<hw>Han"dling</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧n"dl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>handlung</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A touching, controlling,
managing, using, etc., with the hand or hands, or as with the hands. See
<er>Handle</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The heavens and your fair <qex>handling</qex>⟦br⟧
Have made you master of the field this day.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Drawing, Painting, etc.)</fld> <def>The mode of
using the pencil or brush, etc.; style of touch.</def>
<rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>handlock</ent>⟦br⟧
